Explanation:

- The controller function resetPassword handles POST requests to /users/reset.
- It expects a JSON body containing "password" (the new password) and "token" (the reset token previously generated).
- It finds a User by resetToken matching the sent token and with expireToken greater than the current time. If no user is found, it responds with status 422 and JSON { error: "Try again session expired" }.
- On success it hashes the new password, updates the user password, clears resetToken and expireToken, saves the user, and responds with a 200 JSON { message: "password updated success" }.
- The operation does not require authentication and does not return other explicit status codes in the code; I include the two explicit responses observed (200 and 422) and the JSON request body schema with both fields required.

